<span style="color: #000000;">A Unit Council Member is a voluntary dues-paying member of an EAA represented unit, who is elected to serve a three (3) year term. Each EAA MOU (1, 19, 20, and 21) has a five-seat Unit Council that serves as the policy-making group for the unit and helps facilitate communication between the membership, Governors, and EAA Staff.Â </span>
<h3><strong><span style="color: #000000;">EAA Unit Council Members are responsible for:Â </span></strong></h3>
<ul>
	<li><span style="color: #000000;">Assisting Unit Governor and Staff in determining disposition of issues effecting the unit.Â </span></li>
	<li><span style="color: #000000;">Gathering and compiling data on issues.Â </span></li>
	<li><span style="color: #000000;">Receiving negotiating proposals and offering changes from information gathered.Â </span></li>
	<li><span style="color: #000000;">Serving on committees as appointed.Â </span></li>
	<li><span style="color: #000000;">Determining policies and procedures for the unit.</span></li>
</ul>
